de.psi.efload.packerapi
Class LoadingResult

java.lang.Object
  de.psi.efload.packerapi.LoadingResult

public final class LoadingResult
extends java.lang.Object

The result of the packing procedure. A succesful packing procedure delivers a loading plan and an array of transports which could not be allocated because of the capacity limits.

Author:
kschroeder
See Also:
IntegralPacker, IncrementalPacker

Method Detail

assign

public void assign(LoadingResult other)
Assigns another loading result to this result. The loading plan of the other result replaces the loading plan of this result. The unpacked transports of the other result are added to this result's unpacked transports.

Parameters:
other - The result to be assigned to this result.

getUnpackedPackageSets

public PackageSet[] getUnpackedPackageSets()
Returns the package sets containing the fractions of the original package sets which could not be packed into one of the containers.

Returns:
The divided transports containing the package amounts which could not be packed.
